There lived a young lass named Candice Miller, who, after a family misunderstanding, was sent to spend a summer in the quiet Southern town of Lambert, where her stern grandmother had recently passed. There, amidst old belongings, Candice stumbled upon a curious letter addressed to her grandmother, holding within it a perplexing riddle and a faded drawing. This mysterious missive hinted at a grave injustice long past, involving a legendary tennis match, a secret love, and a fortune lost due to ancient prejudices. Thus, with the help of a shy new friend, Candice bravely set forth to unravel the town's hidden history, hoping to solve the perplexing puzzle and right a wrong that had festered for generations.
